"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-08-10-why-so-many-olympic-athletes-are-into-cupping-therapy\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"If you have tuned into the summer Olympics in Paris, you may have watched gymnastSimone Biles add another medal to her resum\\u00e9or swimmerKatie Ledecky snag four.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 51, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999741112336, \"rank\": 2.5888735208521743e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you have been paying particular attention to swimming, you have also likely noticed some of the athletes' bodies are not only adorned with tattoos but also red and purple circular marks that look like bruises or very large hickeys.\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No, they were not attacked by bugs or animals, but instead, these marks result from a wellness therapy known as \\\"cupping,\\\" or myofascial decompression (MFD).\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multi-function_display\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.042465347991053e-11, \"text\": \"MFD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multi-function_display\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multi-function_display\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Cupping is a common technique utilized to treat soft tissue injuries and increase flexibility,\\\" Neal Stepp, senior athletic trainer at Orlando Health Jewett Orthopedic Institute Performance Health, told Salon, adding there are different techniques.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Health\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Orlando Health\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Health\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Health\"}, {\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewett_House\", \"score\": 0.7208531357969389, \"rank\": 0.3872450283769261, \"text\": \"Jewett\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewett_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewett_House\"}, {\"begin\": 758, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.614129110017694e-13, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The most popular cupping technique utilizes a negative pressure soft tissue treatment using suction to manipulate the skin and underlying tissue.\\\"\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Related  Other cupping techniques include utilizing a fire to remove oxygen from the cup causing suction and then utilizing a needle to puncture the skin, suction, and to allegedly release toxins from the punctured skin.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Frequently, Stepp said, Olympics athletes experience soft tissue \\\"irritation\\\" or injuries, and one of the several treatments available for this is cupping.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Athletes who have utilized this technique find it produces great results,\\\" Stepp said.\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Other athletes may not find cupping as effective as other soft tissue treatment options.\\\"\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, he said, the use of cupping depends on the athlete's preferences in treatment along with \\\"accomplishing treatment goals.\\\"\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"By pulling up, it loosens anything tight and stuck, and it draws blood to the area.\\\"\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many athletes swear by it, including Michael Phelps and Olympic gymnastAlex Naddour.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4119157771302475e-33, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also been endorsed by celebrities like Gwneyth Paltrow and Jennifer Aniston.\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Aniston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jennifer Aniston\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Aniston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Aniston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite being popular among celebrities and athletes, Gudrun Snyder, founder of Moon Rabbit Acupuncture, told Salon cupping is not a new health practice - it's a traditional Chinese medicine practice that has been around for thousands of years.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudrun\", \"score\": 0.9999999981164365, \"rank\": 1.4856028481207625e-09, \"text\": \"Gudrun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudrun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudrun\"}, {\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9999999956521606, \"rank\": 4.3360506584012156e-09, \"text\": \"Snyder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.614129110017694e-13, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Traditional_Chinese_medicine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0472248349801892e-20, \"text\": \"traditional Chinese medicine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Traditional_Chinese_medicine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Traditional_Chinese_medicine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When cupping in the modern day, Snyder said practitioners usually take a plastic or glass cup as a suction.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9999999956521606, \"rank\": 4.3360506584012156e-09, \"text\": \"Snyder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In more traditional practices, it is used with fire and bamboo cups, as Stepp explained.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's similar to massage, where massage pushes down, cupping pulls up on the muscle and the muscles and the fascia that connects the muscles and the connective tissue,\\\" Snyder said.\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9999999956521606, \"rank\": 4.3360506584012156e-09, \"text\": \"Snyder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"By pulling up, it loosens anything tight and stuck, and it draws blood to the area.\\\"\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result of the increased blood flow, muscles get looser, and it can help with a range of mobility.\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Swimmers often get a huge build of lactic acid right in their bodies, and they are super sore,\\\" Snyder said.\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2813, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9999999956521606, \"rank\": 4.3360506584012156e-09, \"text\": \"Snyder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Cupping helps the body to detox that lactic acid and get it moved out of the area so that soreness can be relieved.\\\"\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Want more health and science stories in your inbox?\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe to Salon's weekly newsletterLab Notes.\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3010, \"end\": 3015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.614129110017694e-13, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sounds interesting, but what about the bruising?\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And does it hurt?\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Snyder said when done right, it should not feel painful.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"score\": 0.9999999956521606, \"rank\": 4.3360506584012156e-09, \"text\": \"Snyder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ted_Snyder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But one might feel a bit of a \\\"pinch.\\\"\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It might feel \\\"funny,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As if you are being \\\"hugged by an octopus.\\\"\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite anecdotal evidence from some of the world's best athletes, it's natural to wonder if it's just a placebo effect or if there is real science to support this wellness.\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One 2013 study published in the journalPLOS Oneexamined 61 people, finding those with chronic neck pain reported reductions in pain after 12 weeks of treatment.\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When compared to a cohort of people who used a technique called Progressive Muscle Relaxation (PMR), the cupping group reported less pain in the affected area when pressure was applied.\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Cupping massage may however be better than PMR in improving well-being and decreasing pressure pain sensitivity but more studies with larger samples and longer follow-up periods are needed to confirm these results,\\\" the researchers concluded.\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 4053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In aseparate 2012 study, researchers found that people who had arthritis in their knees and underwent cupping reported less pain in 16 weeks compared to those who did not receive any treatment.\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In this exploratory study dry cupping with a pulsatile cupping device relieved symptoms of knee OA compared to no intervention,\\\" the researchers said.\", \"from\": 4249, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Further studies comparing cupping with active treatments are needed.\\\"\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this year, a systematic review in the journalComplementary Therapies in Medicineexamined 11 studies related to cupping effectiveness and reported \\\"high- to moderate-quality evidence that cupping significantly improves pain and disability.\\\"\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4720, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The authors even said \\\"cupping surpasses medication and usual care in reducing pain.\\\"\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 4806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your help to stay independent  Stepp said that there could also be mental health benefits, too, although there have not been any studies examining a direct correlation yet.\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The utilization of cupping to treat soft tissue pain and discomfort could make the athlete feel better,\\\" Stepp said.\", \"from\": 4990, \"to\": 5107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When the athlete feels like their body is being taken care of and is no longer feeling pain and discomfort, the relief of symptoms could have a positive impact on the athlete's mental health.\\\"\", \"from\": 5108, \"to\": 5301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regarding downsides to cupping, Stepp said cupping is considered a \\\"low-risk risk soft tissue treatment.\\\"\", \"from\": 5303, \"to\": 5408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The most common side effect of cupping is bruising, often located directly where the cup is placed,\\\" Stepp said.\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5523, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, bruising is not always present.\", \"from\": 5524, \"to\": 5565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How much pressure is utilized along with soft tissue density and tone impact the possibility of bruising.\\\"\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more  about wellness culture  Copyright \\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 5674, \"to\": 5741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5726, \"end\": 5735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 5737, \"end\": 5740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999999803762878, \"rank\": 1.962373013634019e-08, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited.\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5776, \"end\": 5781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.614129110017694e-13, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SALON \\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 5839, \"to\": 5934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5919, \"end\": 5928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 5930, \"end\": 5933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company